<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Señor
                                    <persName type="to">Infante</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-06-05"><hi rend="italic">June 5,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 16.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Vicuna’s note of January
                            27 last, I have the honor to state that the attorney for the heirs of
                            Patrick Shields is pressing the Department to ascertain when payment
                            will be made of their claim.</p>
                        <p>I have, therefore, the honor to ask that the arrangement reached may be
                            promptly carried out by your Government.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>